  "prompt": "How long can I stay outside the UK as a dependant of the tier2 visa?",
  "response": "As a dependant of a Tier 2 visa holder in the UK, you are subject to certain rules regarding your stay outside the UK. The specific rules can depend on the type of Tier 2 visa your sponsor holds (e.g., Tier 2 General, Tier 2 Intra-Company Transfer, etc.), but generally, the following applies:\n\n1. **Absence from the UK**: If you are a dependant of a Tier 2 visa holder, you can stay outside the UK for up to 180 days in any 12-month period without affecting your visa status. This is the same rule that applies to the Tier 2 visa holder.\n\n2. **Continuous Residence Requirement**: If you are applying for indefinite leave to remain (ILR) in the UK, you must meet the continuous residence requirement. This means you should not be outside the UK for more than 180 days in any 12-month period during the qualifying period for ILR.\n\n3. **Re-entry to the UK**: As long as your visa is still valid and you have not exceeded the 180-day limit, you should be able to re-enter the UK without issues. Always carry your visa and any other required documentation when traveling.\n\nIt's essential to keep track of your time outside the UK to ensure compliance with these rules. If you are unsure about your specific situation or the type of Tier 2 visa your sponsor holds, it's advisable to consult with an immigration lawyer or check the latest guidance from the UK Home Office.",
